              <br><br> <img src="../kanji/kanji_resources/book/Nihongo Challenge Kanji.png" class=" img-fluid website-img">
                <p class="website-detail">It is a workbook which will help you on your kanji journey. Definitely kanji can only be learnt by practice and this books serves the purpose. It has a variety of challenges which will help you get better at basic kanji. 
                  <b> A good choice for JLPT N5 and N4 level</b>.
                  <br><br> <b>Book Link: &nbsp;<a href="https://www.amazon.com/Nihongo-Challege-Japanese-Language-Proficiency/dp/4872177576/ref=sr_1_1?dchild=1&keywords=nihongo+challenge+n5&qid=1591029355&sr=8-1" target="_blank"> Nihongo Challenge Kanji</a> </b>
                </p><br>                  
                  
                <h3 class="heading-text"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Kanzen-Master-Japanese-Language-Proficiency/dp/4883196887/ref=sr_1_1?dchild=1&keywords=kanzen+master+n3+kanji&qid=1591029746&sr=8-1 " target="_blank"><li class="website-heading"> Shin Kanzen Master Kanji</li></a></h3>  
              <br><br> <img src="../kanji/kanji_resources/book/kanzen master kanji N3.jpg" class=" img-fluid website-img">
                <p class="website-detail">As the name suggests, Shin Kanzen Master will definitely help you master the kanji with their book. This book is divided into chapters and gives the reader a lot of practice exercises. 
                  
                 <b> I would recommend using Shin Kanzen Master from JLPT N3 and after </b> because the lower levels do not require that much of practice that these books offer.
                  The amount of practice and vast variety of vocabulary that this book offers is very remarkable, going through the book twice would make you quite comfortable with JLPT N3 vocabulary and kanji.
                  <br><br> <b>Book Link (JLPT N3): &nbsp;<a href="https://www.amazon.com/Kanzen-Master-Japanese-Language-Proficiency/dp/4883196887/ref=sr_1_1?dchild=1&keywords=kanzen+master+n3+kanji&qid=1591029746&sr=8-1 " target="_blank"> Shin Kanzen Master Kanji N3</a> </b>
                  <br><br> <b>Book Link (JLPT N2): &nbsp;<a href="https://www.amazon.com/Kanzen-Comprehension-Japanese-Language-Proficiency/dp/4883195473/ref=sr_1_7?dchild=1&keywords=kanzen+master+n2+kanji&qid=1591029838&sr=8-7  " target="_blank"> Shin Kanzen Master Kanji N2</a> </b>
                  <br><br> <b>Book Link (JLPT N1): &nbsp;<a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/4883195465/ref=sr_1_fkmr0_1?dchild=1&keywords=kanzen+master+n21+kanji&qid=1591029844&sr=8-1-fkmr0" target="_blank"> Shin Kanzen Master Kanji N1</a> </b>

                </p><br>                 
                  
                <h3 class="heading-text"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Nihongo-So-matome-Essential-Practice-Proficiency/dp/4872177304/ref=sr_1_3?dchild=1&keywords=kanzen+master+n3+kanji&qid=1591029746&sr=8-3 " target="_blank"><li class="website-heading">Nihongo So Matome Kanji</li></a></h3>  
              <br><br> <img src="../kanji/kanji_resources/book/Jlpt N3 Nihongo Somatome Kanji.jpg" class=" img-fluid website-img">
                <p class="website-detail">Nihongo So Matome is very good for practicing vocabulary. The book is a weekly lesson based book which covers a few vocab associated with that topic of the day and teaches how those can be used. There are total 6 weeks and each week has 7 days worth of lesson, where lesson 1st to 6th day of each week will teach you some new vocabulary and then test you out with a test at the end of each day lesson. On the 7th day it is compilation test of all the previous days of the week. 
               <br> <b>  I would recommend using Nihongo So Matome from JLPT N3 and after because the lower levels do not require that much of practice that these books offer. </b> <br>
                With a lot of exercises this books helps you practice a lot and get used to use a specific word in what situation. It has a lot of questions which make you accustomed to JLPT question pattern.
                  <br><br> <b>Book Link (JLPT N3): &nbsp;<a href="https://www.amazon.com/Nihongo-So-matome-Essential-Practice-Proficiency/dp/4872177304/ref=sr_1_3?dchild=1&keywords=kanzen+master+n3+kanji&qid=1591029746&sr=8-3  " target="_blank"> Nihongo So Matome Kanji N3</a> </b>
                  <br><br> <b>Book Link (JLPT N2): &nbsp;<a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/4872177274/ref=ox_sc_act_title_1?smid=A130L4HQW02T5Q&psc=1" target="_blank"> Nihongo So Matome Kanji N2</a> </b>
                  <br><br> <b>Book Link (JLPT N1): &nbsp;<a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/487217724X/ref=sr_1_3?dchild=1&keywords=nihongo+so+matome+n1&qid=1591030683&sr=8-3 " target="_blank"> Nihongo So Matome Kanji N1</a> </b>

                </p><br>

