    <p class="website-detail">As the name suggests the Shin Kanzen Master will definitely help you master the vocab with their book. This book is divided into chapters and gives the reader a lot of practice exercises. 
      
     <b> I would recommend using Shin Kanzen Master from JLPT N3 and after </b> because the lower levels do not require that much of practice that these books offer.
      The amount of practice and vast variety of vocabulary that this book offers is very remarkable, going through the book twice would make you quite comfortable with JLPT N3 vocabulary.
      <br><br> <b>Book Link (JLPT N3): &nbsp;<a href="https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/4883197433/ref=ox_sc_act_title_1?smid=APGXEAF4IR5GT&psc=1" target="_blank"> Shin Kanzen Master Vocabulary N3</a> </b>
      <br><br> <b>Book Link (JLPT N2): &nbsp;<a href="https://www.amazon.com/Kanzen-Master-Vocabulary-Language-Proficiency/dp/4883195740/ref=sr_1_1?dchild=1&keywords=shin+kanzen+master+n2+vocabulary&qid=1591694860&sr=8-1 " target="_blank"> Shin Kanzen Master Vocabulary N2</a> </b>
      <br><br> <b>Book Link (JLPT N1): &nbsp;<a href="https://www.amazon.com/Kanzen-Master-Vocabulary-Language-Proficiency/dp/4883195732/ref=sr_1_1?dchild=1&keywords=shin+kanzen+master+n1+vocabulary&qid=1591694910&sr=8-1
        " target="_blank"> Shin Kanzen Master Vocabulary N1</a> </b>

    </p><br>                 
      
    <h3 class="heading-text"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/So-matome-Essential-Practice-Proficiency-Vocabulary/dp/4872177312/ref=sr_1_2?dchild=1&keywords=nihongo+so+matome+n3+vocabulary&qid=1591695201&sr=8-2" target="_blank"><li class="website-heading">Nihongo So Matome Vocabulary</li></a></h3>  
  <br><br> <img src="../vocabulary/vocab_resources/book/so matome.png" class=" img-fluid website-img">
    <p class="website-detail">Nihongo So Matome is very good for practicing vocabulary. The book is a weekly lesson based book which covers a few vocab associated with that topic of the day and teaches how those can be used. There are total 6 weeks and each week has 7 days worth of lesson, where lesson 1st to 6th day of each week will teach you some new vocabulary and then test you out with a test at the end of each day lesson. On the 7th day it is compilation test of all the previous days of the week. 
    <br><b>  I would recommend using Nihongo So Matome from JLPT N3 and after because the lower levels do not require that much of practice that these books offer. </b> <br>
    With a lot of exercises this books helps you practice a lot and get used to use a specific word in what situation. It has a lot of questions which make you accustomed to JLPT question pattern.
    <br><br> <b>Book Link (JLPT N3): &nbsp;<a href="https://www.amazon.com/So-matome-Essential-Practice-Proficiency-Vocabulary/dp/4872177312/ref=sr_1_2?dchild=1&keywords=nihongo+so+matome+n3+vocabulary&qid=1591695201&sr=8-2 " target="_blank"> Nihongo So Matome Vocabulary N3</a> </b>
      <br><br> <b>Book Link (JLPT N2): &nbsp;<a href="https://www.amazon.com/Nihongo-So-matome-Essential-Proficiency-Vocabulary/dp/4872177282/ref=sr_1_1?dchild=1&keywords=nihongo+so+matome+n2+vocabulary&qid=1591695170&sr=8-1" target="_blank"> Nihongo So Matome Vocabulary N2</a> </b>
      <br><br> <b>Book Link (JLPT N1): &nbsp;<a href="https://www.amazon.com/Nihongo-So-matome-Essential-Proficiency-Vocabulary/dp/4872177258/ref=sr_1_1?dchild=1&keywords=nihongo+so+matome+n1+vocabulary&qid=1591695279&sr=8-1" target="_blank"> Nihongo So Matome Vocabulary N2</a> </b>
    </p><br>
